Drought and heat are also a problem for the farmers. European farms expect harvest losses of 30 to 50 percent compared to the previous year. In parts of Germany, the soil is as dry as it has been for 50 years. Extreme drought, thunderstorms and floods often occur together and can severely affect affected countries. Not only in Africa, these extreme weather conditions are increasing but also in Europe, particularly hard hit countries such as Spain and Italy, where massive forest fires and the resulting desertification increases extremely. This year, even European countries such as Germany and Poland are affected, where some regions even introduced emergency harvesting and water restrictions after the second drought. In some regions, rivers and lakes dry up, even the groundwater and drinking water is scarce. Greening Deserts has been reporting extensively on these topics for years, especially in terms of soil degradation and desertification. Large opencast mining areas, large cities (concrete deserts) and urban regions also contribute to this extreme climate. Many of these consequences of man-made climate change are not exactly predictable, but can be estimated very well with today's scientific findings in climate research. We discussed with many climate researchers, nature and environmentalists and exchanged about this problem. http://www.greeningdeserts.com/extreme-weather-in-germany-and-europe-extreme-drought-heat-waves-and-floods

Other topics such as the reform of agriculture, soil improvement and water improvement have been and will be discussed in detail. Unfortunately, we have not received any active and financial support from the responsible authorities since years. For a long time we could do research on more effective cultivation and irrigation methods with a first greening and research camp in the surface mining landscape of Leipzig (Lakeland Neuseenland) - if our inquiries and demands had been taken seriously, especially by the big parties who were informed several times. Our demands and requests for help to over 700 German foundations, especially in the field of education, nature and environmental protection were ignored or there were the usual excuses.

We hope for quick help or support, so that we can work together with all involved parties to make the coal exit and transformation of the energy industry and agriculture to clean energy and technologies (cleantech) fast and efficient. We want to cultivate bamboo, hemp and palm trees on a large scale in opencast mining areas - not just because of the benefits in these areas, but also because of new innovative developments and compensatory measures in relation to global warming. In addition, special desert plants, extremely resistant, robust and undemanding plants are explored, such as rock garden plants and desert bamboo. Thus, many useful plants for improving the quality of soil, air and water can be used not only on land, but also in urban areas and large cities. Of course we will run a diverse agriculture and gardening - this is also called ecofarming. Wild blooms and flowerbeds counteract massive bee and insect deaths or in general the massive extinction of species. As you can see Greening Deserts is not only concerned with deserts and desertification but with many other important tasks and topics. If this is not eligible .. an extensive consultation and accompaniment to appropriate funding would be really appropriate. #desertification #drought #forestation #globalwarming #greening

Dürre und Hitze machen auch den Bauern zu schaffen. Europäische Betriebe rechnen mit Ernteeinbußen von 30 bis 50 Prozent gegenüber dem Vorjahr. In Teilen Deutschlands ist der Boden so trocken wie seit 50 Jahren nicht mehr. Extreme Dürre, Gewitter und Überschwemmungen kommen oft gemeinsam vor und können betroffenen Ländern stark zusetzen. Nicht nur in Afrika steigen diese extremen Wetterlagen sondern auch in Europa, besonders stark betroffen sind Länder wie Spanien und Italien, wo durch massive Waldbrände die Wüstenbildung extrem zunimmt. Dieses Jahr sind sogar Europäische Länder wie Deutschland und Polen betroffen, welche nach der zweiten Dürreperiode sogar Noternten und Wasserbeschränkungen eingeführt haben. In einigen Regionen trocknen Flüsse und Seen aus, sogar das Grundwasser und Trinkwasser wird knapp. Greening Deserts berichtet seit Jahren ausführlich über diese Themen, besonders im Bezug auf Bodendegradation und Desertifikation. Auch große Tagebaugebiete (Tagebauwüsten), große Städte (Betonwüsten) und Urbane Regionen tragen einen Teil zu diesem extremen Klima bei. Viele dieser Folgen bzw. Konsequenzen des menschengemachten Klimawandels sind nicht genau vorherzusehen, aber mit heutigen wissenschaftlichen Erkenntnisen der Klimaforschung sehr gut abzuschätzen. Wir haben mit vielen Klimaforschern, Natur- und Umweltschützern diskutiert und uns über diese Problematik ausgetauscht.

Auch andere Themen wie die Reformation der Landwirtschaft bzw. Agrarwirtschaft, die Bodenverbesserung und Verbesserung der Gewässer wurden und werden ausführlich behandelt. Leider haben wir bis heute keine aktive und finanzielle Unterstützung seitens der verantwortlichen Stellen bekommen. Wir könnten schon lange mit einem ersten Begrünungs- und Forschungscamp im Leipziger Tagebaugebiet und Seenlandschaft an effektiveren Anbau- und Bewässerungsmethoden forschen - wenn unsere Anfragen und Forderungen ernst genommen worden wären, vor allem von den großen Parteien die mehrfach informiert wurden. Auch unsere Bitten und Hilfegesuche an über 700 deutsche Stiftungen, besonders im Bereich Bildung, Natur- und Umweltschutz wurden ignoriert oder es gab die üblichen Ausreden.

Wir hoffen auf schnelle Hilfe bzw. Unterstützung, damit wir mit allen Beteiligten zusammen den Kohleausstieg und Transformation der Energiewirtschaft bzw. Landwirtschaft, zu sauberen Energien und Technologien (Cleantech), schnell und effizient gestalten können. Wir wollen Bambus, Hanf und Palmen im großen Maßstab in Tagebaugebieten kultivieren - nicht nur wegen der Vorteile in besagten Bereichen, sondern auch wegen neuer innovativer Entwicklungen und Ausgleichsmaßnahmen im Bezug auf die Globale Erwärmung. Dazu werden besondere Wüstenpflanzen, extrem resistente, robuste und anspruchslose Gewächse erforscht, etwa Steingartenpflanzen und Wüstenbambus. Somit können viele nützliche Pflanzen für die Verbesserung der Boden-, Luft- und Wasserqualität nicht nur auf dem Land eingesetzt werden, sondern auch in urbanen Räumen und Großstädten. Natürlich werden wir eine vielfältige Landwirtschaft und Gärtnerei betreiben - man nennt dies auch Ecofarming. Wilde Blühstreifen und Blütenbäume wirken dem massiven Bienen- und Insektensterben entgegen. Wie man also sehen kann beschäftigt sich Greening Deserts nicht nur mit Wüsten und Desertifikation sondern mit vielen anderen wichtigen Aufgaben und Themen. Wenn dies nicht förderwürdig ist.. eine umfangreiche Beratung und Begleitung zu passenden Förderungen wäre nun wirklich angebracht.

Aunque no se permite filmar en corte las audiencias realizadas a menores inmigrantes, la productora y creadora cinematográfica Linda Freedman recrea estas escenas en el cortometraje "UNACCOMPANIED CHILDREN: Alone in America", una realidad que se vive a diario: los niños arrestados por ingresar ilegalmente al país no tienen derecho a un abogado designado por el tribunal y tampoco tienen forma de comunicarse o contratar a un representante legal.
Este corto pretende recaudar fondos deducibles de impuestos a través de la organización Immigration Counseling Service (ICS) para pagar abogados que defiendan los casos de cada uno de estos menores.

Although it is not allowed to film in court hearings of immigrant children, the filmmaker and creator Linda Freedman recreates these scenes in the short film "UNACCOMPANIED CHILDREN: Alone in America", a reality that is experienced daily: children arrested for illegally entering the country does not have the right to a lawyer appointed by the court and they have no way of communicating or hiring a legal representative.
This short film aims to raise tax-deductible funds through the organization ICS (Immigration Counseling Service) to pay lawyers to defend the cases of each of these children.

snapshot.title: UNACCOMPANIED Alone in America/ SIN COMPAÑÍA, SOLOS EN AMÉRICA.

YES WE CAN RESTORE A REEF IN ONLY FEWS YEARS !

With this technique, we will soon no longer need nurseries!
This fast-growing technique can be use to mass-produce reef-building corals and to transplant them to dead or dying reefs that have taken centuries to develop!

This can slow down or even reverse the alarming loss of corals.
In 1 year or 2 years, it could become a dive site.
The goal is to create "in a very short time a reef like the reefs decades ago.No need to wait a century.
We have just given a try and we will show you their evolution in the coming months!

Corals will continue to grow on nurseries and around December, when the temperature of the water will be colder, it is not 100 or 500 corals that we will transplant but thousands with the help of biologists with whom we are working and we hope if we have the financial means to bring them to our island and thus serve as an example of what could be done in the Caribbean soon!

Thanks to Marine Biologist Liza Carne of Fragments of Hopes, Diego Lirman Biologist Dr. Diego Lirman's Reef Restoration Laboratory of Biology of Austin Bowden-Kerby Coral for Conservatrion and of course biologist David Vaughan of Mote Marine Lab

Thank you all for your support! Because more than ever, after the recent phenomena that touched us, we need your support for all for our future and those of our children!

Thank you to the sailing school SaintBarth Yacht Club for the boat made available as well as the place!

We will never say it enough, for lack of financial means, it will be impossible in the near future to continue our actions. So that we can continue on land as well as on sea, if you wish to give us financial help, go to the link below:
http://www.coral-restoration-stbarth.com/donation.html

markup.__html:
YES WE CAN RESTORE A REEF IN ONLY FEWS YEARS !

With this technique, we will soon no longer need nurseries!
This fast-growing technique can be use to mass-produce reef-building corals and to transplant them to dead or dying reefs that have taken centuries to develop!

This can slow down or even reverse the alarming loss of corals.
In 1 year or 2 years, it could become a dive site.
The goal is to create "in a very short time a reef like the reefs decades ago.No need to wait a century.
We have just given a try and we will show you their evolution in the coming months!

Corals will continue to grow on nurseries and around December, when the temperature of the water will be colder, it is not 100 or 500 corals that we will transplant but thousands with the help of biologists with whom we are working and we hope if we have the financial means to bring them to our island and thus serve as an example of what could be done in the Caribbean soon!

Thanks to Marine Biologist Liza Carne of Fragments of Hopes, Diego Lirman Biologist Dr. Diego Lirman's Reef Restoration Laboratory of Biology of Austin Bowden-Kerby Coral for Conservatrion and of course biologist David Vaughan of Mote Marine Lab

Thank you all for your support! Because more than ever, after the recent phenomena that touched us, we need your support for all for our future and those of our children!

Thank you to the sailing school SaintBarth Yacht Club for the boat made available as well as the place!

We will never say it enough, for lack of financial means, it will be impossible in the near future to continue our actions. So that we can continue on land as well as on sea, if you wish to give us financial help, go to the link below:
http://www.coral-restoration-stbarth.com/donation.html

Yes we can restore a reef in only fews years !

Avec cette technique nous pourrons prochainement plus avoir besoin de nurseries !

Cette technique de croissance rapide, peut permettre de produire en masse des coraux de construction de récifs pour les transplanter sur des récifs morts ou mourants qui ont pris des siècles pour se développer !

Ce qui peut ralentir ou même inverser la perte alarmante de coraux.

Dans 1 an ou 2, il pourrait devenir un site de plongée. Le but, est de créer "dans un très court laps de temps un récif comme les récifs il y a des décennies.

Pas besoin d'attendre un siècle.

Nous avons juste fait un essai et vous montrer leur évolution dans les mois qui viennent ! les coraux continueront de pousser sur les nurseries et vers le mois de décembre quand la température de l'eau sera plus froide ce n'est pas 100 ou 500 coraux que nous allons transplanter mais des milliers avec l'aide des biologistes avec lesquels nous travaillions et que nous espérons si nous avons les moyens financiers de leur faire venir sur notre ile et ainsi servir d'exemple de ce qui pourrait être entrepris dans la Caraïbe prochainement !

Merci à la Biologiste Marin Liza Carne de Fragments of Hopes du Biologiste Diego Lirman Dr. Diego Lirman's Reef Restoration Laboratory de Floride du Biologsite Austin Bowden-Kerby Coral for Conservatrion et bien sur le biologiste David Vaughan du Mote Marine Lab

Merci à vous tous pour votre soutien ! car plus que jamais après les récents phénomènes qui nous ont touché nous avons besoin de votre soutien à tous pour notre futur et ceux de nos enfants !

Merci à l'école de voile le SaintBarth Yachtclub pour le bateau mis à disposition ainsi que l'endroit !

Nous ne le dirons jamais assez, par manque de moyens financiers, il nous sera impossible dans un futur proche de poursuivre nos actions. Pour que nous puissions continuer sur terre comme sur mer si vous souhaitez nous apporter une aide financière ,rendez-vous sur le lien ci-dessous :

http://www.coral-restoration-stbarth.com/donation.html

Amigos
O momento brasileiro exige que a comunidade esteja unida e coesa.
As diferenças do passado devem ser relevadas a segundo plano, em busca do lugar comum: Judaísmo e Sionismo!
Temos certeza que a comunidade deseja eleger nossos candidatos nas próximas eleições, a nível estadual e federal.
Atendendo a um gentil convite do candidato a presidente nas próximas eleições da FIERJ, eu e MARCELO ITAGIBA almoçamos com ARY BERGHER.
A foto retrata a total cordialidade que nos aproximou e saímos unidos pelo bem maior que temos em comum: a nossa comunidade.
Itagiba é pré-candidato a deputado federal e Tereza Bergher a deputada estadual.
Tenham certeza que no Rio não haverá lugar para o racismo ou o antissemitismo travestido de antissionismo.
Estaremos todos unidos e vigilantes!!!
Shalom, Salam, Paz....

28.06 - Dia Internacional do Orgulho LGBT
🏳️‍🌈✨❤️

Que o amor vença o preconceito, as barreiras e os padrões. Que sejamos todos livres pra amar sem medo. O amor é lindo em todas as suas versões.

Fica aqui minha homenagem a esse dia tão especial e importante para a comunidade LGBT. Obrigada a toda minha equipe LM Music que idealizou e se entregou a esse projeto com tanto carinho. Obrigada DJ JP por produzir a música com tanto cuidado. Obrigada principalmente aos meus fãs que se propuseram a fazer parte desse vídeo. Eu tô só emoção vendo tudo isso pronto ❤️😭

Assista ao clipe completo clicando aqui: bit.ly/UmPoucoDeCor
